<div id="review_12281888" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/12281888" />
    <a title="Thenicole" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/185193-thenicole"><img alt="Thenicole" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1201982375p2/185193.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/12281888?book_show_action=true">Jan 11, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Thenicole" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Thenicole" href="/user/show/185193-thenicole">Thenicole</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer12281888" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5161665250737644034">Thankless task, to try to write a review of Mahfouz. Simply put, he&apos;s a master of Islamic writing, a master of personality, of human folly, and even in translation he puts most of us to shame. Whereas you&apos;d expect something kind of sweet, this bitter book is utterly human; which is to say, it is about cruelty and pettiness and the lives of those who live to closely together. <br/>Flawless.</span>
  <span id="freeText5161665250737644034" style="display:none">Thankless task, to try to write a review of Mahfouz. Simply put, he's a master of Islamic writing, a master of personality, of human folly, and even in translation he puts most of us to shame. Whereas you'd expect something kind of sweet, this bitter book is utterly human; which is to say, it is about cruelty and pettiness and the lives of those who live to closely together. <br />Flawless.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5161665250737644034" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

